"{\"uid\": \"dailypost.ng-2024-08-08-paris-olympics-2024-bostwanas-tebogo-wins-gold-medal-in-200m-final\", \"text\": \"Published  on  By  Letsile Tebogo from Bostwana produced a shock at the Paris 2024 Olympics on Thursday, winning gold in the 200m final.  The 21-year-old claimed the 200m gold medal, denying Noah Lylesa a sprint double at the competition.  Tebogo also finished with an African record of 19.46 seconds.  American Kenneth Bednarek came second, crossing the line in 19.62 seconds.  Lyles, who became the world's fastest man by five-thousandths of a second in the 100m final on Sunday night, matched his Tokyo bronze in 19.70 seconds.  It emerged after the race that Lyles had tested positive for COVID-19 and the 27-year-old had to be helped off the track in a wheelchair.  Ex-Chelsea manager Pochettino in pole position to coach national team  Paris 2024 Olympics: Brume fails to win medal in women's long jump  Paris Olympics 2024: Tobi Amusan Nigeria's major hope of winning medal  Paris Olympics 2024: Lineup for Team Nigeria event as Amusan, Ogazi, D'tigress, others compete  Paris Olympics 2024: France to play Spain in men's football final  Paris Olympics 2024: Nigeria's Favour Ofili qualify for Women's 200m semifinals  Paris Olympics 2024: Sports Minister commends two Nigerians for advancing to 100m semi-final  WAFCON 2022: Super Falcons up against South Africa, Burundi, Bostwana in group C  Copyright \\u00a9Daily Post Media Ltd\"}"